## 5. Boat Controller System

### 5.1 Rationale
Using a rigid-body physics engine (Rapier) is overkill and introduces jitter. We need deterministic, smooth movement.

### 5.2 Implementation Approach
Pure kinematic math executed inside the `requestAnimationFrame` loop. The state tracks `velocity` and `rotation`.

### 5.3 Pseudocode
```typescript
class BoatController {
    speed = 0;
    maxSpeed = 0.5;
    acceleration = 0.02;
    drag = 0.95; // Friction multiplier
    rotationSpeed = 0.03;

    constructor(private app: App) {}

    update(delta: number) {
        // Thrust
        if (this.app.input.keys.up) {
            this.speed = Math.min(this.speed + this.acceleration, this.maxSpeed);
        } else if (this.app.input.keys.down) {
            this.speed = Math.max(this.speed - this.acceleration, -this.maxSpeed / 2);
        }

        // Apply Drag
        this.speed *= this.drag;

        // Rotation (Only allow turning if moving)
        if (Math.abs(this.speed) > 0.01) {
            const turnMultiplier = this.speed > 0 ? 1 : -1;
            if (this.app.input.keys.left) this.mesh.rotation.y += this.rotationSpeed * turnMultiplier;
            if (this.app.input.keys.right) this.mesh.rotation.y -= this.rotationSpeed * turnMultiplier;
        }

        // Apply Velocity to Position
        this.mesh.position.x += Math.sin(this.mesh.rotation.y) * this.speed * delta;
        this.mesh.position.z += Math.cos(this.mesh.rotation.y) * this.speed * delta;

        // Visual Bobbing (Math.sin)
        this.mesh.position.y = Math.sin(this.app.time.elapsed * 0.002) * 0.2;
    }
}
```

### 5.4 Risks & Mitigations
*   **Risk:** Frame rate drops cause the boat to teleport or move at inconsistent speeds.
*   **Mitigation:** Always multiply velocity translations by the `delta` time passed from the loop.

