## 7. Island System

### 7.1 Rationale
Loading a 20MB GLB file containing all 5 regions at once will cause a 10-second blank white screen, violating our "Zero Friction" FTUE (First Time User Experience) pillar.

### 7.2 Implementation Approach
**V1 Loading Strategy.** We will use `Promise.all()` to load all V1 assets during startup. The user is presented with a loading screen until all assets are ready, preventing them from interacting with a half-broken world.

### 7.3 Pseudocode
```typescript
class IslandSystem {
    constructor(private app: App) {}

    async init() {
        const models = ['island_hub.glb', 'archipelago.glb', 'monoliths.glb', 'reef.glb', 'harbor.glb'];
        const loadPromises = models.map(file => this.loadModel(`/assets/models/${file}`));
        
        const chunks = await Promise.all(loadPromises);
        
        for (const chunk of chunks) {
            chunk.matrixAutoUpdate = false;
            chunk.updateMatrix();
            this.app.scene.add(chunk);
        }
        
        this.app.events.emit('loadingComplete');
    }
}
```

### 7.4 Risks & Mitigations
*   **Risk:** Loading all assets synchronously increases initial load time.
*   **Mitigation:** Profile first, optimize later. V1 contains only ~15 low-poly models heavily compressed with Draco. Complex background asset streaming is a premature optimization and is deferred to V2.

