## 8. Interaction System

### 8.1 Rationale
We need to trigger HTML Modals (Resume Mode popups) when the boat gets near an island. Using 3D Raycasting against high-poly island meshes every frame is extremely expensive.

### 8.2 Implementation Approach
**2D Radial Proximity Detection.** We ignore the Y-axis entirely. We calculate the 2D distance (X and Z) between the Boat and an invisible "Trigger Point" placed at the center of each island.

### 8.3 Pseudocode
```typescript
class InteractionSystem {
    triggers = [
        { id: 'project_1', x: 100, z: 120, radius: 15, active: false },
        { id: 'harbor', x: 200, z: 300, radius: 20, active: false }
    ];

    constructor(private app: App) {}

    update() {
        const boatPos = this.app.world.boat.mesh.position;

        for (const trigger of this.triggers) {
            // Fast 2D distance check (Pythagorean theorem)
            const dx = boatPos.x - trigger.x;
            const dz = boatPos.z - trigger.z;
            const distance = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dz * dz);

            if (distance < trigger.radius && !trigger.active) {
                trigger.active = true;
                this.app.events.emit('openModal', trigger.id);
            } else if (distance >= trigger.radius && trigger.active) {
                trigger.active = false;
                this.app.events.emit('closeModal', trigger.id);
            }
        }
    }
}
```

### 8.4 Risks & Mitigations
*   **Risk:** The trigger radius is too small, and the user sails past without noticing.
*   **Mitigation:** Add a visual indicator (a glowing ring on the water or a floating UI prompt) that scales up as the user approaches the radius edge.

