## 11. Whale Event System

### 11.1 Rationale
The Cosmic Whale must feel cinematic, but we cannot afford a complex AI system or skeletal rigs. It must be hardcoded to perfection.

### 11.2 Implementation Approach
A state machine triggered when the boat crosses a specific `Z` coordinate boundary (e.g., leaving the Monoliths). We use `GSAP` to animate the static mesh along a bezier curve.

### 11.3 Pseudocode
```typescript
import gsap from 'gsap';

class WhaleSystem {
    hasBreached = false;
    mesh: THREE.Mesh; // Low-poly static whale mesh

    constructor(private app: App) {}

    update() {
        if (this.hasBreached) return;

        const boatZ = this.app.world.boat.mesh.position.z;
        if (boatZ > 150) { // Deep water threshold
            this.triggerBreach();
        }
    }

    triggerBreach() {
        this.hasBreached = true;
        this.app.audio.fadeForWhale();

        // Position whale directly under the boat
        const boatPos = this.app.world.boat.mesh.position;
        this.mesh.position.set(boatPos.x, -50, boatPos.z + 20);

        // Cinematic GSAP arc
        gsap.to(this.mesh.position, {
            duration: 4,
            y: 30, // Apex of the jump
            z: boatPos.z + 80,
            ease: "power2.out",
            onComplete: () => {
                // Crash back down
                gsap.to(this.mesh.position, {
                    duration: 3,
                    y: -50,
                    z: boatPos.z + 120,
                    ease: "power2.in",
                    onComplete: () => this.spawnSplashParticles()
                });
            }
        });
        
        // Pitch rotation
        gsap.to(this.mesh.rotation, {
            duration: 7,
            x: -Math.PI, // Full front-flip barrel roll
            ease: "power1.inOut"
        });
    }
}
```

### 11.4 Risks & Mitigations
*   **Risk:** The whale jumps but the user is looking the wrong way.
*   **Mitigation:** The isometric camera is locked. We explicitly code the whale to jump *in front* of the boat's current velocity vector.

